      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Modern historians generally view the UN's effectiveness in preventing major 21st-century conflicts as highly mixed, leaning toward limited success. While the UN has played a crucial role in peacekeeping and humanitarian intervention in some regions, its structural limitations, particularly the veto power of the Security Council, often paralyze action when great power interests conflict. Therefore, consensus suggests it is a necessary but frequently constrained institution, not a foolproof guarantor of global peace.",
